# probe_time.ct — the SYSTEMS-BRIDGE probe (Mission C0). A TEST FIXTURE, not
# shipped game content: a toy §7 timed system that ticks in-game through
# ContourBridge and is asserted bit-identical to lattice-cli's own tick.
#
# `Fade` reads two mirror keys (probe.start, probe.target) and writes one
# (probe.level) as a REAL `over 3.0s` construct — the body sweeps probe.level
# from start to target across three seconds on the normalized clock `t`. Driven
# by the injected clock (ContourBridge.tick(dt) -> lattice_tick), it suspends
# into a serializable continuation (Fade.__time) that survives every tick and
# every save/restore, so the scene test can snapshot mid-`over`, restore, and
# prove the completion is byte-identical (the replay law, in-process).
system Fade:
	reads: probe.start, probe.target
	writes: probe.level
	sim func step():
		over 3.0s:
			probe.level = lerpf(probe.start, probe.target, t)
